data.text: Joan McSheehy competed in the 100 backstroke at the 1932 Los Angeles Olympics, finishing fifth. She was second at the 1932 US Olympic Trials. McSheehy competed for the Womenâ€™s Swimming Association in 1932. She was US Indoor Champion in the 100 yard backstroke. She later married and became Joan Huffman, but died fairly young, at age 34.
